args:
Once Nimis devours Valerio's sandwiches,
the situation shifts in his favor, and Valerio
emerges from the fierce competition victorious.
After the contest, he and Mitsuba treat the
prince and friends to a lunch made with all
of their gratitude.
Is Picaro trying to use Nimis to make\na mess of the entire competition?!
No, that's not it! He's going to—
Oho ho ho, Nimis! Try THIS, if you would!\nSample the amazing wares of Picaro!
Want Nimis eat this? Look tasty.
I knew it! He's planning to have Nimis eat\nall his food and end this in one fell gulp!
So THIS is why he's been feeding\nthat dragon night after night!
Predicting and preparing for any and all\nhardships is the essence of a first-rate\nchef! Oho! Ohooo ho ho ho ho!
And what part of you is supposed\nto be a ＂first-rate chef,＂ exactly?
Quiet, you! This has assured my victory!\nNow go stick your thumb in a humble pie\nwhile you behold my great triumph!
Aaaaagh! I can't bear to watch!
But wait... No! This is not yet over!\nThe plates are not returned!
And you will never get them back\nfrom the gut of that fool dragon!
He's spitting the plates out like\nwatermelon seeds! Which means...
The first contestant to gather up one\nthousand plates is...VALEEEEERIO!
It's a miraculous turnabout for Valerio!\nHe is the new Orichalcum Chef!
Maybe you'll understand how this\nhappened if you try one of Valerio's\nleftover sandwiches.
Do you mistake me for a coarse laborer?\nWould you ask Picaro to dig a ditch next?\nScrub a pot? WASH MY OWN APRON?!
Ugh, just shut up and pick one already.\nWe've got plenty of kinds to choose from.
Pick...one...? By my exalted cheese grater!\nDo you mean to say that each sandwich\nIS COMPLETELY DIFFERENT?!
Yep. Every plate has a different sandwich\nwith different ingredients and flavors.\nWe made a thousand unique tastes.
You were driven into the proverbial corner\nand STILL managed such feats?!
I kept saying it was too much work\nand it couldn't possibly be done...
But Valerio stuck it out. He had a plan,\nand he stuck to it no matter what.
He thought about how to please each\nand every one of his thousand eaters.\nTHAT is his resolve.
And that's also how you know this one\nright here is gonna be good. Now open\nup and try it already!
N-no! Picaro would never lower himse—
SHUT UP AND EAT THE DAMN SANDWICH!
*nibble* I-impossible... To think one could\nget this flavor from a lowly hoagie!
Such taste! Such texture! Such skill!\nI experience your resolve in every bite!
Well, it looks like we've finally reached\nthe end of this story. Great job, everyone!
I put you to untold amounts\nof trouble from start to finish.
Yes, but at least we got a few\namazing meals out of it!
So what's next for the two of you?\nIs it back to Hinomoto, Mitsuba?
No. Nothing would change if\nI went home as I am now.
I need to train a bit more here in Alberia\nso I can be the world's best next time.
No! The world's best will be PICARO!
I had something I wanted\nto say before I leave...
Valerio! From this day forth, you and\nPicaro are BITTER RIVALS!
No ordinary chef can be your nemesis.\nThe only one fit to go toe-to-toe with you\nis Picaro, the cheatiest of cheats!

I will master my underhanded techniques
to become the perfect dastard! And when
next we meet in the field of kitchen battle,
I will SLAY YOU! Oho ho ho ho!
For I can hardly let my dear boy see his\nfather in a state of such weakness, no?
Wait, you're serious? You don't see any\nproblem with letting him see you compete\nas a total cheat?
Leave it be, Mitsuba. He listens about as\nwell as a sack of sprouted potatoes.
Until the day we meet again...\nFarewell, my rival!
Well, he's clearly learned his lesson.
So what's on your agenda, eh, Valerio?\nGonna go on a journey to different places\nand open up a buncha franchises?
I am indeed in a position where\nsuch a thing is possible now.
But I thought it also might be nice to\nremain here and run a single, simple\nestablishment all my own.
There are many unusual ingredients to be\nfound here, but more importantly, it is\nhome to people of all races.
It is an ideal place for seeing what\nkinds of food various people like.
Hey, if it means I get to eat more of yer\nchow, I hope ya stay put forever!
Then perhaps you can start with this.
Me and Valerio made you all lunch\nas our way of saying thanks.
Did I die and go to meet the Goddess?\nTwo Orichalcum Chef competitors went\nand made ol' Ranzal LUNCH?!
Heck yeah, food! Time to meet my belly!
By all means, please eat your fill.
We'd be glad to. I'm grateful for the\nbounty Alberia has provided us, as well\nas for how thoughtful you chefs are.
Why is it you passed over Picaro's food\nand ate only Valerio's, Nimis?
I do, indeed: pea soup and\nbream meunière.
What's wrong? That's no way to act\nwhen offered food.
If you're going to be like that, you don't\nget to have this fruit compote I brought\nfor dessert.

Ack! You ate the whole thing in one gulp!
Hmm... You used to eat anything and
everything, so is it possible my desserts
have given you a sweet tooth?

The only sweets left during the tournament
were those dessert-like sandwiches.
So that means the reason you ate all
Valerio's food was because...
